Package: remedia
Version: 1.0.0
Section: utils
Priority: optional
Architecture: all
Maintainer: Vladislav <v.krashevski@gmail.com>
Depends: bash (>= 5.0), coreutils
Recommends: util-linux, findutils
Description: Remedia - media-oriented system extension
 Remedia is a modular system designed to extend Debian/Ubuntu-based environments
 for media production, user data archiving, and system recovery.
 Remedia CLI system - modular CLI framework with runtime, registry and module system.
 Provides mediasystem, mediapanel, backupkit, and system tooling.
 It provides both CLI and UI interfaces. The UI can be launched with:
  remedia system center
 Key components include:
  * MediaSystem: configurable pipeline for media workflows
  * MediaPanel: media production
  * Backupkit: user recovery system
 System configuration is stored in:
  /etc/remedia/remedia.env
 Remedia introduces a manifest-driven system state model.
 The Manifest module acts as a trust anchor when system becomes unreliable.
